 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Applied Scientist SK hynix America San Jose, CA 95134 Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Company Overview 
Gauss Labs, specializing in industrial artificial intelligence (AI), aims to revolutionize manufacturing through innovative AI technologies. SK hynix, the second largest memory chip maker in the world and the biggest affiliate of the South Korean conglomerate SK Group, is investing $55 million in Gauss Labs to drive SK Group’s future value creation and to transform its own operations by utilizing a vast amount of data generated at multiple sites of the manufacturing company. Founded in August 2020 and headquartered in San Jose, California, Gauss Labs has also opened a Korean office in Seoul. 
For more information, please visit to the website: www.gausslabs.ai 
Job title:  Applied Scientist 
 Location:  San Jose, CA, USA 
 
 
 Key Responsibilities: 
Gauss Labs is seeking a passionate and talented Applied Scientist who will collaborate with other scientists and engineers to leverage AI, Machine Learning (ML), and optimization methods to solve diverse problems in manufacturing and other industries. 
As a Gaussian Applied Scientist, you will design and run experiments, develop new algorithms, and find new ways of reducing cost and maximizing performance and reliability of manufacturing systems. Besides theoretical analysis and innovation, you will work closely with seasoned scientists, engineers, and program managers to deliver his/her algorithms and models into real products. Your work will directly impact our customers in manufacturing lines. 
The ideal candidate is enthusiastic about delivering products and solutions that are robust and dominant in the market. You thrive in ambiguous environments that require to find best answers to open problems that have not been solved before. You leverage your exceptional technical expertise in fast-paced research and development, as well as your fundamental understanding of computer science, mathematics, and statistics, to create reliable, scalable, and high-performance products. Your strong communication skills enable you to work effectively with both business and technical partners. You have hands-on experience making the right decisions about technical methods. You strive for simplicity and elegance, and demonstrate significant creativity and sound judgment backed by real data. Most of all, you are willing to take calculated risks, learn by trying, and grow as a team. 
Basic Qualifications 
BS/MS/PhD degree in Statistics, Computer Science, Machine Learning, Industrial Engineering, Operational Research, Data Science, Electrical Engineering, Mathematics, or a related field 
Practical experience applying machine learning to solve complex problems 
Hands-on experience programming in Python, Matlab, R, Java, C#, C++, or other similar programming languages 
Proficiency in algorithm and model development, model validation, and model implementation for large-scale applications 
Experience distilling customer requirements into problem definitions, dealing with ambiguity, and competing objectives with perseverance 
Strong communication and data presentation skills 
Ability to develop practical solutions to complex problems 
Preferred Qualifications 
Extensive experience applying theoretical models in an applied environment 
Strong fundamentals in problem solving, algorithm design, and complexity analysis 
Up-to-date understanding of industry and technology trends in the area of research 
Contribution to Gauss Labs' Intellectual Property pools through patents and/or external publications 
Clear understanding of business contexts for decisions made within and across groups 
Strong personal interest in learning, researching, and creating new technologies with customer impact 
Superior verbal and written communication and presentation skills, ability to convey rigorous mathematical concepts and considerations to non-experts 
Proven track record in technically leading and mentoring scientists as well as engineers SK hynix America 30+ days ago original job Report job Scientist jobs in San Jose, CA Jobs at SK hynix America in San Jose, CA Scientist salaries in San Jose, CA Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
